All Known Implementing Classes:

public interface NamedStreamsProvider
extends ResourceWrapper

Provider of named streams. This provider provides a map with NamedStream objects.

getSharedStream

NamedStream<?> getSharedStream(String name)
                               throws InitializationException
A global stream is a stream that is shared by more than one NamedStreamsProvider instances. These streams may be closed when all NamedStreamsProvider instances accessing them have #close() invoked.

Parameters:
name - Stream name.
Returns:
Returns the stream.

InitializationException

convert

NamedStream<?> convert(String nameOfStreamToConvert,
                       StreamType typeOfNewStream,
                       String nameOfNewStream)
                       throws DataException
Creates a new stream by converting the stream with the specified name that is managed by this NamedStreamsProvider to the specified StreamType. The new named stream is automatically registered to this NamedStreamsProvider.

Parameters:
nameOfStreamToConvert - Name of the stream that will be converted.
typeOfNewStream - Type of the new NamedStream.
nameOfNewStream - Name of the new stream.
Returns:
Returns a new NamedStream with the specified name of new stream.
Throws:
DataException -
  • If this NamedStreamsProvider does not support the specified conversion.
  • If this NamedStreamsProvider does not manage a stream with the specified name.
